==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{AHD|hīd}}, {{IPA|/haɪd/}}, {{SAMPA|/haId/}}
*{{audio|en-us-hide.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aɪd}}

===Etymology 1===
{{OE.}} {{term|hydan|hȳdan}} (a weak verb; strong endings in modern English come by analogy with {{term|ride}} etc.).

====Verb====
{{en-verb|hides|hiding|hid|hidden}}

# {{transitive}} To put (something) in a place where it will be harder to [[discover]] or [[out of sight]].
#: ''He '''hides''' his magazines under the bed.''
#: ''The politicians were accused of keeping information '''hidden''' from the public.''
# {{intransitive}} To put oneself in a place where one will be harder to find or out of sight.

=====Synonyms=====
*(1): [[conceal]], [[hide away]], [[secrete]]
*(2): [[go undercover]], hide away, hide oneself, [[hide out]], [[lie low]]

=====Antonyms=====
''Transitive:''

*[[disclose]], [[expose]], [[reveal]], [[show]], [[uncover]]

''Intransitive:''
*reveal oneself, show oneself

