===Etymology 2===
{{OE.}} {{term|hyd|hȳd}}, from {{PG.}} *{{term||hūđiz}}, from {{PIE.}} *{{term||kūtis}}.  Cognate with Dutch {{term|huid}}, German {{term|Haut}}; and with Latin {{term|cutis}}, Ancient Greek {{term|κύτος||sc=polytonic}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{countable}} The [[skin]] of an [[animal]].
# {{countable}} {{italbrac|mainly British}} A covered [[structure]] from which hunters, birdwatchers, etc can observe animals without [[scare|scaring]] them.
# A medieval land measure equal to the amount of land that could sustain one free family; usually 100 [[acre]]s. Forty hides equalled a barony.

